Details:
Job Description

Must-have skills: 5+ y of QA testing and reporting exp; exp implementing and/or testing in one or more of the following: People Soft Financials (Financials); Human Capital Management (HCM) ; Oracle Analytics Cloud (OAC) and Oracle Business Intelligence Applications (OBIA); exp with automated testing tools such as PeopleSoft Test Framework (PTF) and/or TestGrid and/or Tosca; gov/finance exp, HCM, Financials, DW/OBIA, Microsoft Office suite, SharePoint, Visio, Smartsheet.

Requirements

Experience implementing and/or testing in one or more of the following:
Experience People Soft Financials
Human Capital Management (HCM)
Oracle Analytics Cloud (OAC) and Oracle Business Intelligence Applications (OBIA)
Experience performing QA activities directly related to validating ERP implementation.
Experience performing QA testing and reporting.
Experience with automated testing tools such as PeopleSoft Test Framework (PTF), TestGrid, Tosca.
Experience analyzing systems requirements to identify QA needs.
Experience developing unit test cases and test plans as well as requirements tracking and reporting results.
Experience in the use of Microsoft Office suite, SharePoint, and Visio.
Experience using Smartsheet or other similar collaboration tools.

Preferred

Experience performing activities directly related to QA Experience working with the State or with other large government entity (5+ years);
Experience with QA Testing Financials, HCM and OAC.
Experience with PeopleTools 8.59+ and fluid page development.
Working with functional and technical resources to identify testing scenarios, including expected results.
Experience developing QA plans.
Experience in one or more QA area (Ex: HCM, Financials, DW/OBIA)
Bachelor’s Degree in Computer Science, Information Systems, Information Technologies, Business Management, Accounting, or related field.

Responsibilities Include But Are Not Limited To The Following

Take day-to-day direction from the QA Lead and work with Project team members to complete activities related to QA;
Use and share lessons learned and best practices associated with the area of QA that may promote efficiency and help identify and mitigate potential risks;
Serve as a QA subject matter expert, which includes:
Developing QA guidelines and procedures;
Developing and executing QA test scripts, including regression scripts, for the comprehensive solution;
Documenting and reporting test results;
Conducting regression testing following changes migrating to the system testing or user-acceptance testing environments;
Assisting in developing and execute interface and integration testing strategies, guidelines, procedures, and scripts;
Assisting with other testing services as requested;
The testing services include assisting with the following but are not limited to:
Financials and Payroll implementations;
Data warehouse/business intelligence implementations;
Data cleansing and conversion;
Data integration;
System Reporting;
System, integration, and end-user testing;
Cutover planning and execution;
Complete knowledge transfer/training activities to the identified parties;
Provide overall Project support, which includes:
Providing updates as appropriate for Project status reporting;
Coordinating with the Directors, Architects, and the Project Management Office to develop/update templates for Project use;
Facilitating meetings, promoting teamwork, and providing training as requested;
Tracking, mitigating, and escalating risks, and issues; and
Maintaining testing tools for the Project team’s use.
Perform other duties as assigned;
Assist the Project to troubleshoot and resolve issues in the production system;
Conduct work (and ensure that any tools, templates, or applications are developed) in accordance with the standards and specifications;
Complete transition services, including facilitating lessons-learned meetings; creating a lessons-learned document related to QA support services; and providing all the documents, software, software licenses, and other Project artifacts to the Project team.
